<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-27T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-27T12:00:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2638</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Austria-Hungary</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PFC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Penfield</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-27T18:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 28, 6 p.
                                    m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1242. Transacting business yesterday at Ministry of Foreign Affairs,
                                Minister deliberately said: “I do not want you to go from Austria.”
                                Many unofficial Austrians have expressed to me opinion that break
                                with America would be madness.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFC1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Penfield</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>